				<p>I don't know what videos you refer to. But The white circles are landmarks, and the walls are just walls with landmarks on them. Think about the word "marker" it doesn't mean anything particular, anything can be a "marker": a door handle marks a door, an X marks the spot, etc. Landmarks are just markers which are useful for mapping. They can be corners (which are easily recognized by lasers), or color blobs (which are easily recognized by cameras). The term landmark is flexible and determined by *you* the algorithm designer.</p>
